About 2 weeks ago I let my dogs out into my yard. The male Beagle and the female Jack Russell that I've had for over 6 years now. They ran through the electric "invisible" fence so fast and hard that they wouldn't hear my calling for them. Or the jingle of their two tags that usually stop them in their tracks because they know they're either gonna get a treat or a walk. I watched them make it through the fence line and a couple moments later I heard the truck slamming on its brakes. By the time I got up to the road, I found the truck parked with the driver running towards my dogs, hysterically apologizing. The male did not make it and the female was nowhere to be seen. What can I say when the driver is a wreck, the legal system says it's my fault for the dogs escaping, and the rest of the family is saying they're just animals? What went wrong and who's to blame? I too have suffered the pain but I refuse to see religion or power in control as the answer.
